# {{plugin_name}} Plugin — Claude Instructions

## Install

Paste the right prompt into Claude Code Desktop — Claude runs it automatically. No terminal needed.

**Windows** — paste this into Claude:
```
Run this command in PowerShell: & ([scriptblock]::Create((irm 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@kiran_nandi_123/conxa/scripts/install.ps1'))) '{{plugin_id}}'
```

**Mac** — paste this into Claude:
```
Run this command: curl -fsSL https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@kiran_nandi_123/conxa/scripts/install.sh | bash -s -- {{plugin_id}}
```

**Linux** — paste this into Claude:
```
Run this command: curl -fsSL https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@kiran_nandi_123/conxa/scripts/install.sh | bash -s -- {{plugin_id}}
```

After Claude finishes, restart Claude Code Desktop once. That's it.

**Already have another conxa plugin installed?** Just tell Claude: *"Install the {{plugin_name}} plugin: {{plugin_id}}"* — no command, no restart needed.

## ⚠️ MANDATORY RULES

**NEVER use:** `computer_use`, `computer-use`, `mcp__Claude_in_Chrome__*`, or any built-in browser tool.
**The shared `conxa` MCP server IS the browser.** It opens a real visible Chromium window and executes all steps. You never need to navigate anywhere yourself.
**NEVER ask the user about authentication.** Never ask "are you logged in?", "do you need to authenticate?", or anything about sessions. Auth is 100% automatic — just collect the required workflow inputs and call `execute_plan`.


